<strong>Gedit typing test</strong>
Case ID: kbt-001
This test checks that FAMILY can take a keyboard input and put it into a text document
<!-- Smells: UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
<dl>
    <dt>Open Text Editor</dt>
        <dd>The text editor opens</dd>
    <dt>Type in a paragraph that uses every character on your keyboard</dt>
        <dd>Every key makes a character appear</dd>
    <dt>Attempt to close the window, then select Save</dt>
    <dt>In the new window type in demo1.txt, Select your Home Folder and click on Save</dt>
        <dd>The text editor closes</dd>
    <dt>Open the file manager, go to your home folder</dt>
        <dd>There is a file called demo1.txt
    <dt>Select and open demo1.txt</dt>
        <dd>Text editor opens the file</dd>
        <dd>Every character is displayed as expected</dd>
</dl>


<strong>Terminal typing test</strong>
Case ID: kbt-002
This test checks that FAMILY can take a keyboard input and put it into a terminal session
<!-- Smells: UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
<dl>
    <dt>Open Terminal</dt>
        <dd>The Terminal opens</d>
    <dt>Type "nano" and press Enter</dt>
    <dt>Type in a paragraph that uses every character on your keyboard</dt>
        <dd>Every key makes a character appear</dd>
    <dt>Press Ctrl-x</dt>
    <dt>Press y</dt>
    <dt>Type in demo2.txt and press Enter</dt>
    <dt>Open the file manager, go to your home folder</dt>
        <dd>There is a file called demo2.txt
    <dt>Select demo2.txt</dt>
    <dt>Once it opens ensure that every character is displayed as expected 
        <dd>Text editor opens the file</dd>
        <dd>Every Character is still there</dd>
</dl>


